  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "\n<p><b>Type:</b> Ninjutsu (Doton)</p>\n<p><b>Rank:</b> 6</p>\n<p><b>Chakra Cost:</b> 6</p>\n\n<p><b>Learn DC:</b> 18 | <b>Successes:</b> 2</p>\n<p><b>Perform:</b> 8 | <b>Perform DC:</b> 19</p>\n\n<p><b>Components:</b> H, F</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>Created to compliment the use of the Daichi Shokujou no Jutsu, this technique is an empowered form of its counterpart Douheki no Jutsu. This technique may only be used on firm or hard earthen ground, such as stone, and the user must be able to slam his earthen mace directly against the ground. The ground splits forward to the point under the targeted area, where it explodes. This attack deals 3d10 points of earth damage to any creature standing directly on it, damage increasing by an additional 1d10 against prone creatures or creatures currently beneath the earth, as the ground bursts apart violently. Damage from this technique can be halved with a successful reflex save.</p>\n\n<hr><p><b>Requires:</b> Daichi Shokujou no Jutsu (3)</p>\n<p><b>Material Focus:</b> Earthen mace.</p>\n",
